title: Severn Head Dart
info: The head dart (EyeSlugger) is a cosmic dart installed on the head of the Great Sima, which is 0.77 meters long when it is huge to two meters (one meter of the Great Sima is equal to two meters of others). After throwing the head dart, the Sima controls the head dart to fly in the air through the brain waves of the crooked force Babu, and can fly white-hot to the enemy to carry out onion chicken to the enemy. After the onion chicken is finished, it will reverse back to the Sima's head. It can also be used as a dagger to cut a knife. Because the dart can adjust its power, it can sometimes only injure but not cut off enemies, as is the case with reckless starmen and small boss starmen. In the 10th episode, the head dart also showed the power of directly penetrating the enemy's body, defeating the skin swallow star. In the 49th episode, when he was captured by the enemy's Iron Head Baby Kensei, the Sima controlled the head dart with the brain wave of Ba Bu, making the head dart turn around and kill the Kensei. Head dart and Malaysia ray, male ketone ray tied for the three major signature skills of Sima, the canyon destroyed a large number of team-mates big bird. However, it is not effective against enemies who can effectively defend against this move, such as the enemy of life. title: Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics Mascot-Bingdun Dun
info: The mascot of Beijing Winter Olympic Games, Bingdun Dun, is designed and created based on panda. The panda image is combined with the ice crystal shell with super energy, reflecting the characteristics of winter ice and snow sports and modern science and technology. The head shell is modeled from the ice and snow sports helmet and decorated with colorful halo. It is inspired by the "Ice Ribbon" of the National Speed Skating Hall of Beijing Winter Olympic Games. The flowing bright color lines symbolize the track of ice and snow sports and 5G high-tech;The heart-shaped pattern on the left palm represents the warm welcome of the host country to friends from all over the world. The overall image resembles an astronaut, implying extraordinary creation and exploration of the future, reflecting the pursuit of excellence, leading the times and facing the infinite possibilities of the future.

title: The central government calls for strengthening anti-monopoly, which has deep meaning
info: Kang Hui: Today's headline highlights the meeting of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee. The meeting explicitly mentioned the need to strengthen anti-monopoly and prevent disorderly capital expansion. At present, some platforms engage in "big data familiarity," and some platforms force small merchants to "choose one from two" when conducting promotional activities, etc. Not long ago, the State Administration of Market Supervision, in the draft for comments, plans to make big data familiar and other practices, clearly defined as abuse of dominant market position behavior, to carry out strict supervision. Once a monopoly is formed in a certain field, it will hinder competition and harm consumers 'rights and interests. When the main body of the market is active, consumers will have more choices and the economic cycle will be more active.

info: This week's upload is everyone's favorite,"Detective Conan Theme Song"! This particular theme song plays in the background whenever Conan catches a criminal (usually kicking something very hard) in the climax of the show. Basically, this is the same as "There is only one truth!" I've improvised this piece many times in my live gigs, but this week, I decided to choreograph an official version. A bit of searching on the web, I was surprised to find that the music for each of the 23 conan theatres is quite different, each with a unique instrument, slight melodic modifications and a unique bridge. Most of the time, the main melody is played by the most distinguished saxophone, but there are also versions played by trumpets, electric guitars, violins, horns, etc. It's really hard to choose from all these variations, so I ended up combining three representative versions. The opening prelude is probably the most well-known rhythm, as it is also used in the TV series (and also in the fourth theatrical version). The second interlude at 01:06, which has a unique flow, was only included in the theatrical version of parts 5, 6 and 9, but this is my personal favorite rhythm. Finally, the third interlude was introduced at 02:11. This is probably the most popular variation to date, as it has been used in more than 10 theatrical releases so far. The energy between the beats is particularly intoxicating, which is why I ended up with it as the theme song. Unfortunately, I couldn't add any more bridge parts to this adaptation because there were so many variations to choose from. I think I'm going to improvise these bridge parts in future concerts. All right, that's it. I hope you can all enjoy my Detective Conan theme song with three different interludes! I think next week I'll do another old anime song. Everybody stay safe, and as always, see you next week!¬†Animenz---------------------------------Myfacebookpage:http://www.facebook.com/AnimenzFollowmeonTwitter! https://twitter.com/AnimenzzzIamusingInstagramaswell! https://www.instagram.com/animenz_official/--------------------------------PianoarrangementbyAnimenz OriginalSong:MainTheme/Meintesma Anime:DetectiveConan(TVseries)/Detective Conan Published by:PolyGram(1996) Composed by:KatsuoOhno/KatsuoOhno Performed by:KatsuoOhnoBand/KatsuoOhno
